At  Meme 100x Bot, we are committed to protecting your privacy. This Privacy Policy outlines how we collect, use, and safeguard your personal information when you use our bot. By using the bot, you agree to the collection and use of your information in accordance with this Privacy Policy.

1. Information We Collect
When you interact with the Bot, we may collect certain types of information:

Personal Information
Discord User Information: We may collect your Discord username, user ID, and any other information you provide when you interact with the Bot. This data is used primarily for bot interaction and identification purposes.
Usage Data
Interaction Data: We may collect data about your interactions with the Bot, such as commands issued, messages sent, and other actions taken during use. This helps us improve the functionality of the Bot and provide better service.
Log Data
System Logs: We may collect logs of system interactions, including errors, crashes, or performance data. This is used for troubleshooting and improving bot performance.
2. How We Use Your Information
We use the information we collect to:

Provide and improve the Bot's services.
Ensure the bot operates smoothly, including debugging and troubleshooting.
Communicate with users (e.g., for bot updates or bug fixes).
Prevent abuse or malicious activities.
3. Data Storage and Security
Data Storage: The data we collect is stored on secure servers, and we take reasonable measures to ensure it is protected.
Data Retention: We may retain your data as long as you use the Bot. You can request that your data be deleted by contacting us (see the "Contact" section).
Security: We employ reasonable administrative, technical, and physical safeguards to protect your data from unauthorized access or disclosure.
4. Data Sharing and Disclosure
We do not sell, rent, or share your personal information with third parties, except in the following cases:

Legal Requirements: We may disclose information if required to do so by law or in response to legal requests.
Service Providers: We may use third-party services (e.g., hosting or logging providers) that help us operate the Bot. These service providers have access to your information only to perform specific tasks and are obligated not to disclose or use it for other purposes.
5. Cookies and Tracking Technologies
We do not use cookies or tracking technologies on the bot. However, some third-party services we use (such as analytics or hosting services) may use cookies on their platforms. We encourage you to review the privacy policies of those services to understand how they use cookies.

6. User Control and Data Access
You have control over your data and can:

Request Data Deletion: If you want your data to be deleted, you can contact us at kpckpc470@gmail.com. We will delete your data in accordance with applicable laws.
Opt-Out: If you no longer want to interact with the Bot, you can remove or block the Bot from your server.
7. Changes to This Privacy Policy
We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. When changes are made, we will update the Effective Date at the top of this page. Continued use of the Bot after changes to this policy will constitute your acceptance of the updated terms.

8. Children's Privacy
The Bot is not intended for users under the age of 13, and we do not knowingly collect personal data from users under 13. If we discover that we have collected personal data from a child under 13, we will take steps to delete that information as quickly as possible.

9. Governing Law
This Privacy Policy shall be governed by and construed in accordance with the laws of India, without regard to its conflict of law principles.

